over  million of additional capital for csp’s growth has been provided through our network of high net worth individuals and institutions along with iroquois’ continued participation in each round of equity offerings in early  iroquois created its investment banking group to provide mergers and acquisitions advisory and private capital raising services for middle market companies iroquois expanded its platform of specialty finance services and created iroquois financial partners i lp “ifp i” which provided credit support for loans made to early stage companies in need of capital affording qualified investors the opportunity to invest in growthstage companies investors in ifp i were given the ability to realize a return on an “underutilized” asset–their personal credit this is different than the typical committed capital arrangement in  iroquois created an additional alternative investment opportunity for qualified investors by merging ifp i into iroquois financial partners ii lp “ifp ii” ifp ii provides qualified investors the same opportunities as ifp i but on a much larger scale iroquois has a long and successful track record of providing debt and equity capital and offering investment banking services to middle market companies and providing alternative investments for our base of high net worth individuals and institutional investors  back to top  west end avenue suite  nashville tn  phone  fax infoiroquoiscgcom investments are made available and offered through our brokerdealer iroquois capital advisors llc a wholly owned subsidiary and finra and sipc member business continuity plan privacy policy usa patriot act iroquois  news  iroquois capital group — nashville home portfolio companies transaction history professionals contact navigation portfolio companies transaction history professionals icg team advisory board contact us categories news news iroquois capital group launches next venture nashville business journal december   scott harrison – another busines